This folder contains three subdirectories - each containing an example with known issues running, and thus is for the interest of the developers of FETCH2.

All three run using the bugle96 data library, and this needs to be inserted to the folder before running (bugle96 is not contained here).

All three contain the .geo file so that a mesh can be generated locally. The two examples demonstrating a segmentation fault also contain a mesh which I have generated on my machine. The example demonstrating convergence issues on Archer does not contain a mesh, that must be generated locally on your machine - as well as a mesh decomposition.

###############################################################################
###############################################################################
###############################################################################

200817_beamline_no_adapt

This example has had convergence issues on Archer. The mesh decomposition did not make any difference to these issues for me - I tried various combinations of finer meshes and coarser meshes decomposed into small numbers and large numbers of regions using fldecomp. 

This example runs on Archer, but never manages to converge, and thus uses up all available wall time without getting anywhere.

###############################################################################
###############################################################################
###############################################################################

Beamlinecentimetres_SEGFAULT

This example segfaults - but changing the coarsening method fixes it.

